"Well, they say it's all about how you look at things." [l][r]
I say to my own reflection in the darkened shop window as I head toward the station. [l][r]
A businessman-like man walking ahead looks at me in surprise, so I flash a quick smile and say in a broken tone, "Just talking to myself." [l]It's handy to play the clueless foreigner sometimes.[l][r]
[cm]My reflection in the glass is sagging. Still, I force myself to smile. A smile, Yuri. That's my only skill. [l][r]
It's okay to feel lonely sometimes. Eventually, we all have to become adults and face society alone. [l][r]

[_tb_end_text]

