("That doesn't sound like you," I thought.) [l][r]
The reflection in the glass seems to criticize. My smile turns stiff and forced.[l][r]
[r]("Weren't you the one who only cared about the present, not the past or the future? That's your philosophy, isn't it?") [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3]
...I don't care. That's a thought from my past. I'm not interested. [l][r]
I'd do anything to be happy now. I'm not good at thinking about the future, but if it's necessary for my current happiness, I'll do it. [l][r]
[r]("That sounds just like Chii-chan.") [l][r]
Of course. Chii-chan and I are like one being. There's a piece of her in me and a piece of me in her. [l][r]
We realized it when we climbed those steps together and reached the top. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

